{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id788e3242-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s275"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"275"},"text":"§ 275.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Hiring critical technical experts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id788e3243-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s275/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The officers and employees of the Institute, except the director, shall be appointed by the Secretary at such time as their respective services may become necessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id788e3244-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s275/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Hiring critical technical experts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3104"},"text":"section 3104 of title 5","children":[],"tail":" or the provisions of any other law relating to the appointment, number, classification, or compensation of employees, the Secretary shall have the authority to make appointments of scientific, engineering, and professional personnel, and to fix the basic pay of such personnel at a rate to be determined by the Secretary at rates not in excess of the highest total annual compensation payable at the rate determined under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t3/s104"},"text":"section 104 of title 3","children":[],"tail":". The Director shall appoint not more than 15 personnel under this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id788e3245-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s275/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sunset","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The authority under section ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002144"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002144"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “subsection”."}],"tail":" (b) shall expire on the date that is 5 years after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-08-09"},"text":"August 9, 2022","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id788e3246-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1901-03-03/ch872/s6"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1901, ch. 872, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/1450"},"text":"31 Stat. 1450","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1903-02-14/ch552/s10"},"text":"Feb. 14, 1903, ch. 552, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/32/829"},"text":"32 Stat. 829","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-03-04/ch141/s1"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1913, ch. 141, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/736"},"text":"37 Stat. 736","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tV/s5115/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title V, § 5115(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1433"},"text":"102 Stat. 1433","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/167/dB/tII/s10244"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–167, div. B, title II, § 10244","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/1488"},"text":"136 Stat. 1488","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id788e3247-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id788e3248-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id788e3249-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-08-09"},"text":"August 9, 2022","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (c), was in the original “the date of the enactment of this section”, which was translated as meaning the date of enactment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/167"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–167","children":[],"tail":", which amended this section generally, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id788e324a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/167"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–167","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The officers and employees of the Institute, except the director, shall be appointed by the Secretary of Commerce at such time as their respective services may become necessary.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Institute” for “bureau”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id788e324b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id788e324c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-03-04"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1913","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Secretary of Commerce” for “Secretary of Commerce and Labor”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id788e324d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1903-02-14"},"text":"Feb. 14, 1903","children":[],"tail":", transferred power and authority of Secretary of the Treasury over Bureau of Standards to Secretary of Commerce and Labor."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id788e324e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Procurement of Temporary and Intermittent Services","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/69/tIII/s3009"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–69, title III, § 3009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/592"},"text":"121 Stat. 592","children":[],"tail":", permitted the Director of the National Institute of Standards and Technology, until "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 2010","children":[],"tail":", to procure the temporary or intermittent services of no more than 200 experts or consultants per year to assist with urgent or short-term research projects and required the Comptroller General to submit to Congress, no later than 2 years after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2007","children":[],"tail":", a report on possible additional safeguards needed should the authority under this section be made permanent."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id788e324f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Demonstration Project Relating to Personnel Management","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/574/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–574, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3238"},"text":"100 Stat. 3238","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tV/s5115/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title V, § 5115(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1433"},"text":"102 Stat. 1433","children":[],"tail":", directed the Office of Personnel Management and the National Institute of Standards and Technology to jointly design an alternative personnel management system demonstration project to be commenced not later than "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1988","children":[],"tail":", and to be conducted by the Director of the Institute in accordance with "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s4703"},"text":"section 4703 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees, with the Director of the Office of Personnel Management to provide that the project be evaluated annually by a contractor, and a report of the contractor’s findings submitted to the Office, and, along with any comments of the Office and the Institute, submitted to the Congress, and a final report to be submitted to the Congress by the Comptroller General not later than 4 years after the date on which the project commences, such report to include any recommendations for legislation or other action considered appropriate by the Comptroller General."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"[","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/113/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–113, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-03-07"},"text":"Mar. 7, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/779"},"text":"110 Stat. 779","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/104/113/s10"},"text":"“The personnel management demonstration project established under section 10 of the National Bureau of Standards Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1987 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/574"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–574","children":[],"tail":"] ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s275"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 275","children":[],"tail":" note) is extended indefinitely.”"}],"tail":"\n]"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
